    "created_at": "2012-07-26T23:43:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-07-26T23:43:39Z",
    "body": "Yeah. The hard/soft thing has never been implemented, as far as I know, but I think it's the best we can do: retain correctness of our memory model and _try_ to retain correctness of user code, but not at the cost of infinite-recursion. If their dtor itself fails, just unwind that sub-failure w/o the opportunity for sub-sub-failures.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
