    "created_at": "2013-10-25T04:06:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-10-25T04:06:46Z",
    "body": "The scheduler does have logic for not failing from linked failure when a task is already failing. So if, for example, the sleeping destructor here were to happen during unwinding, I think it should be fine. But if it happens normally you could still get failure.\n",
